{
  "stem": "24515.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Let me put it this way, I'm, to this day, rather pleased that there was no American psychologists, like me, or social worker, or anything like that around.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because if there had been, I would have quite clearly had been diagnosed with a major nervous breakdown.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I suppose what happened was, I tried to grow up enormously quickly.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "What I did do was, I hung around the center of the camp, and anybody who would listen to me, you know, who would talk to me, I would tell of how urgent it was to get my parents out and my brother.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Right?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And indeed, as it happened-- that's a rather long, and complex story-- but there-- as it happened, a woman very-- you know, working in the refugee departments, in the-- in the offices, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] interested himself-- herself, and somehow, by hook or by crook, and it really was being the crook, [? sought ?] that-- that my brother came.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So he came-- I mean, I arrived in England, February the 8th.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He came as in May 5.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "February, March, April-- wait, two or three months later, he did come.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, it's a long story.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The lady, this-- this woman, this English woman, Ms.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Macobi, OK, who was a secretary in the refugee organizations, whom I hated with bitterness.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Macobi.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Macobi, Ms.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Macobi said he'd [INAUDIBLE] my brother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she told me in a little while that she's found a sponsor.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I wanted to know who that sponsor was, and thank him, meet him, and so on, so on, and she waved me off.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Turns out the sponsor was a nice little Jew, who'd signed anything they asked him to.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He couldn't have sponsored my brother anymore than he-- than he could have sponsored himself.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
